data.name: sec.desc
data.value: Time of 9192631770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the Cesium 133 atom at 0 °K.

data.name: db.desc
data.value: A logarithmic unit used to express the ratio of two values of a physical quantity, often power or intensity.

data.name: radian.desc
data.value: The plane angle subtended by a circular arc as the length of the arc divided by the radius of the arc. 1 rad

data.name: steradian.desc
data.value: The solid angle subtended at the center of a sphere of radius r by a portion of the surface of the sphere having an area r². A sphere encompasses 4π sr.

data.name: m.desc
data.value: The length of the path travelled by light in vacuum during a time interval of 1/299792458 of a second.

data.name: parsec.desc
data.value: The distance at which one astronomical unit subtends an angle of one arcsecond

data.name: au.desc
data.value: roughly the distance from Earth to the Sun

data.name: diopter.desc
data.value: A unit of refractive power that is equal to the reciprocal of the focal length (in meters) of a given lens.

data.name: kg.desc
data.value: The mass of the international prototype of the kilogram.

data.name: kelvin.desc
data.value: The fraction 1/273.16 of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water.

data.name: amp.desc
data.value: The constant current needed to produce a force of 2×10-7 newton per metre between two straight parallel conductors of infinite length and negligible circular cross-section placed one metre apart in a vacuum.

data.name: cd.desc
data.value: The luminous intensity of a source that emits monochromatic radiation of frequency 540×10^12 hertz and that has a radiant intensity in that direction of 1/683 watt per steradian.

data.name: mole.desc
data.value: The amount of substance which contains as many elementary entities as there are atoms in 0.012 kilogram of carbon 12, defined to be 6.022 x 10^23 molecules, atoms, or some other unit.

data.name: equivalent.desc
data.value: The amount of a substance that reacts with (or is equivalent to) an arbitrary amount of another substance in a given chemical reaction.

data.name: molarity.desc
data.value: Number of moles of solute per litre of solution.

data.name: joule.desc
data.value: The work done when a force of one newton moves the point of its application a distance of one metre in the direction of the force.

data.name: ev.desc
data.value: The amount of energy gained (or lost) by the charge of a single electron moving across an electric potential difference of one volt.

data.name: faraday.desc
data.value: The magnitude of electric charge per mole of electrons.

data.name: wh.desc
data.value: One watt consumed in one hour

data.name: watt.desc
data.value: The power which in one second of time gives rise to one joule of energy.

data.name: coulomb.desc
data.value: The amount of electricity carried in one second of time by one ampere of current.

data.name: e.desc
data.value: The charge of a single electron.

data.name: volt.desc
data.value: The difference in electric potential across two points along a conducting wire carrying one ampere of constant current when the power dissipated between the points equals one watt.

data.name: ohm.desc
data.value: The resistance between two points in a conductor when one volt of electric potential difference, applied to these points, produces one ampere of current in the conductor.

data.name: farad.desc
data.value: The capacitance between two parallel plates that results in one volt of potential difference when charged by one coulomb of electricity.

data.name: weber.desc
data.value: Magnetic flux which, linking a circuit of one turn, would produce in it an electromotive force of 1 volt if it were reduced to zero at a uniform rate in 1 second.

data.name: henry.desc
data.value: The inductance of a closed circuit that produces one volt of electromotive force when the current in the circuit varies at a uniform rate of one ampere per second

data.name: celsius.desc
data.value: The scale of temperature in which water freezes at 0° and boils at 100° under standard conditions.

data.name: unit.desc
data.value: The amount that catalyzes the conversion of 1 micro mole of substrate per minute

data.name: light.desc
data.value: velocity of light in a vacuum

data.name: ly.desc
data.value: The distance that light travels in a vacuum in one Julian year

data.name: carat.desc
data.value: metric carat is defined as 200 mg exactly

data.name: gas.desc
data.value: Molar, universal, or ideal gas constant

data.name: kcd.desc
data.value: a measure of how well a light source produces visible light

data.name: rankine.desc
data.value: Scale of absolute temperature primarily used in thermodynamics.

data.name: fahrenheit.desc
data.value: Pure water is defined to freeze at 32 °F

data.name: troy_oz.desc
data.value: Commonly used to measure the mass of precious metals

data.name: slug.desc
data.value: A mass that accelerates by 1 ft/s² when a force of one pound (lbf) is exerted on it.

data.name: lbf.desc
data.value: The pound-force is equal to the gravitational force exerted on a mass of one avoirdupois pound on the surface of Earth.

data.name: btu.desc
data.value: The amount of heat required to raise the temperature of 1 avoirdupois pound of liquid water by 1 degree Fahrenheit at a constant pressure of one atmosphere.

data.name: rpm.desc
data.value: The rotational speed of a mechanical component.

data.name: hubble.desc
data.value: The constant of proportionality between the distance to a galaxy and its velocity
